tweet: I’ve occupied all sorts of body shapes and sizes throughout my journey to recovery, and while I absolutely agree that general comments about body size are not okay, I think it’s absolutely okay to be concerned for someone whose body has changed quickly.

name: clara rehmann
description: raising a bearded dragon, writing in Python. PhD student at UofO ( she/her 🏳️‍🌈 #actuallyautistic )
tweet: and are often “picked up on” following dramatic weight loss. It’s absolutely okay to be concerned for someone you love who is losing weight quickly, as that is usually never good for a body (eating disorder or otherwise). 2/n

name: clara rehmann
description: raising a bearded dragon, writing in Python. PhD student at UofO ( she/her 🏳️‍🌈 #actuallyautistic )
tweet: So, I’ve struggled with anorexia for over half my life, and have been seeing people say today that it’s never okay to acknowledge someone’s sudden/drastic weight loss. Cruel comments about bodies are never warranted, but eating disorders are a secretive disease 1/n
